  <title>Find a Time Record</title>

  <p>The <gui style="tab">Time Records</gui> tab will not show all time records, to make viewing easier and faster.  Instead, you have to search for time records using a start and end date as criteria.</p>

  <p>You may also filter the results by specifying a branch or employee.</p>

  <p>To search for time records:</p>
  <steps>
    <item><p>Log in to the Control Panel.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click the <gui style="tab">Time Records</gui> tab.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">Edit</gui><gui style="menuitem">Find</gui></guiseq>, or press <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>F</key></keyseq>, or click <gui style="button">Find</gui> in the toolbar.</p></item>
    <item><p>Set the start and end dates, set the branch or employee if needed, then click <gui style="button">Find</gui>.</p></item>
  </steps>

